{
  "texts": [
    "Executing these actions within the environment, which, depending on the case study, might involve selecting movements or adjusting joint angles crucial to the study.3.",
    "Receiving feedback in the form of rewards, which are calculated by taking into account both the execution time and the diversity of explored scenarios.4.",
    "Utilizing this feedback to improve the agent's decision-making for future actions.A key component of our training process is the implementation of a moving average on the rewards received by the agent.",
    "This technique helps in smoothing out short-term fluctuations and highlighting longer-term trends in performance.",
    "Training is deemed complete when there is no noticeable improvement in the moving average of the rewards, indicating that the agent has reached an optimal learning state."
  ]
}